<article title='List_of_Anglo-Saxon_monarchs_and_kingdoms'><paragraph><template><target>unreferenced</target><arg name="date">February 2013</arg></template></paragraph><paragraph><template><target>Anglo-Saxon society</target></template>A succession of monarchs ruled the various independent kingdoms which arose in<space/><link><target>Anglo-Saxon England</target><part>England</part></link><space/>following the<space/><link><target>end of Roman rule in Britain</target></link><space/>in the 5th century. The most prominent of these kingdoms were<space/><link><target>Kingdom of Kent</target><part>Kent</part></link>,<space/><link><target>Kingdom of East Anglia</target><part>East Anglia</part></link>,<space/><link><target>Kingdom of Sussex</target><part>Sussex</part></link>,<space/><link><target>Wessex</target></link>,<space/><link><target>Mercia</target></link><space/>and<space/><link><target>Northumbria</target></link>, with each kingdom often recognising their own monarch.</paragraph><paragraph>The early genealogies are based on the (semi-historical)<space/><link><target>Anglo-Saxon royal genealogies</target></link><space/>as compiled in the 9th century.</paragraph><heading level='2'>Anglo-Saxon kings</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem>See the<space/><link><target>:Category:Anglo-Saxon monarchs</target><part>Anglo-Saxon monarchs category</part></link>.</listitem></list><heading level='3'>Kings of East Anglia</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem>See<space/><link><target>List of monarchs of East Anglia</target></link></listitem></list><heading level='3'>Kings of Essex</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem>See<space/><link><target>Kingdom of Essex</target></link></listitem></list><heading level='3'>Kings of Kent</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem>See<space/><link><target>List of monarchs of Kent</target></link></listitem></list><heading level='3'>The Kings of Mercia</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem>See<space/><link><target>List of monarchs of Mercia</target></link></listitem></list><heading level='3'>The Kings of Northumbria</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem>See<space/><link><target>List of monarchs of Northumbria</target></link></listitem></list><heading level='3'>Subkingdoms of Northumbria</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem><link><target>Bernicia</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Deira (kingdom)</target><part>Deira</part></link></listitem></list><heading level='3'>Kings of Sussex</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem>See<space/><link><target>List of monarchs of Sussex</target></link></listitem></list><heading level='3'>Kings of Wessex</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem>See<space/><link><target>List of monarchs of Wessex</target></link></listitem></list><heading level='3'>Other minor kingdoms</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem><link><target>Kingdom of Ynys Weith</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Kingdom of the Iclingas</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Kingdom of Lindsey</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Hwicce</target></link></listitem></list><paragraph><template><target>Heptarchy</target></template></paragraph><paragraph><template><target>DEFAULTSORT:Anglo-Saxon Monarchs</target></template><link><target>Category:Anglo-Saxon kingdoms</target><part>List</part></link><link><target>Category:Anglo-Saxon monarchs</target><part>List</part></link><link><target>Category:Lists of former countries</target></link><link><target>Category:Lists of monarchs</target></link></paragraph></article>